            "answer_text": "When determining the mass of a given number of moles of a substance, multiply the given moles by the molar mass of the substance. For O2, the molar mass is 2 \u00d7 its atomic weight on the periodic table in grams per mole (g/mol). Molar mass of O2 = 2 \u00d7 15.999 g/mol = 31.998 g/mol 1.5 mol O2 \u00d7 (31.998 g O2/1 mol O2) = 48 g O2 to two significant figures ",
